==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bottom fermentation
<hw>Bot"tom fer`men*ta"tion</hw>. <def>A slow alcoholic fermentation
during which the yeast cells collect at the bottom of the fermenting
liquid. It takes place at a temperature of 4⟦deg⟧ - 10⟦deg⟧ C. (39⟦deg⟧
- 50⟦deg⟧F.). It is used in making lager beer and wines of low alcohol
content but fine bouquet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

